# Real-Life Problem: Body Mass Index (BMI) Calculation
# Question:
# Calculate the Body Mass Index (BMI) based on the weight and height of a person.
# Take these values as input from the user.

# Answer:
weight_person = float(input("Enter the weight of the person (in kilograms): "))
height_person = float(input("Enter the height of the person (in meters): "))

# Calculate BMI using the formula: BMI = weight / (height^2)
bmi_person = weight_person / (height_person**2)
print("Body Mass Index (BMI):", bmi_person)
